---
title: Fregula Sarda & Sweet Italian Sausage with Wilted Spinach & Baby Portobellos
description: Fregula Sarda is a Sardinian pasta made from coarse Semolina flour. Its nutty, rustic character pairs perfectly with sweet sausage and woodsy thyme. Tossed with portobellos and topped with garlicky spinach, the dish has weeknight comfort food written all over it.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/55253f0e6ced6e63508b4567.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/55253f0e6ced6e63508b4567.pdf
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 650 kcal
  fat: 48 g
  carbohydrates: 21 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 4 g
cuisine: Italian
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/fregula-sarda-sweet-italian-sausage-55253f0e6ced6e63508b4567
course: main course
servings: 2
---

Halve, peel, and finely chop the @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Slice the @mushrooms{4%oz}. Thinly slice the @garlic{2%clove}(thinly sliced). Strip the @thyme{1%sprig} leaves off the sprig, then finely chop. Remove the @sweet Italian pork sausage{9%oz} from the casings.

Heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large #pan{} over medium heat. Add the sausage and onion to the pan and cook, breaking up the pieces, for about ~{3-4%minutes}, until sausage is browned but not yet cooked through.

Add the mushrooms, half the garlic, and thyme to the pan with the sausage and cook, tossing, ~{4-5%minutes}, until softened. Add the @fregula sarda{3/4%cup} and stir for about ~{1%minute} to lightly toast. Add @water{2%cups} and the @veggie stock concentrate{1} and bring to a boil. Reduce to a simmer, and cook for about ~{15%minutes}, until fregula sarda is tender with a bit of bite to it.

Meanwhile, heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a medium pan over medium heat. Add the remaining garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Add the @spinach{5%oz} and cook, tossing, about ~{2-3%minutes}, until wilted. Add a splash of water, if necessary. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir the @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} into the fregula sarda mixture and serve in #bowls{} topped with the wilted spinach.